The paper deals with DNA codes, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves establishing a one-to-one correspondence between elements of a ring and DNA codewords, which is a combinatorial problem (cs.DM). The paper also discusses distance-preserving maps, which are relevant to coding theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions optimal codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and the construction of new codes, which is relevant to signal processing (cs.SI).
